{"header":"<h1>Module <code><span>Soteria.Solvers</span></code></h1>","type":"documentation","uses_katex":false,"breadcrumbs":[{"name":"Index","href":"../../../index.html","kind":"leaf-page"},{"name":"soteria","href":"../../index.html","kind":"page"},{"name":"Soteria","href":"../index.html","kind":"module"},{"name":"Solvers","href":"#","kind":"module"}],"toc":[],"source_anchor":null,"preamble":"<p>Low-level solver manipulation and utilities.</p><p>The main interface is <a href=\"Solver_interface/module-type-S/index.html\"><code>Solver_interface.S</code></a>, which defines the interface that SMT solver backends must implement to be used with the symbolic execution engine. This signature assumes the solver is mutable.</p><p>A solver relies on a value encoding, which is defined by the <a href=\"Value/module-type-S/index.html\"><code>Value.S</code></a> signature as a way to encode values and types into SMT-LIB.</p><p>Soteria then provides an implementation of this interface for Z3 in <a href=\"Z3/index.html\"><code>Z3</code></a>; more backends are planned for the future.</p>","content":"<div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec module anchored\" id=\"module-Solver_interface\"><a href=\"#module-Solver_interface\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">module</span> <a href=\"Solver_interface/index.html\">Solver_interface</a></span><span> : <span class=\"keyword\">sig</span> ... <span class=\"keyword\">end</span></span></code></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec module anchored\" id=\"module-Value\"><a href=\"#module-Value\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">module</span> <a href=\"Value/index.html\">Value</a></span><span> : <span class=\"keyword\">sig</span> ... <span class=\"keyword\">end</span></span></code></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec module anchored\" id=\"module-Z3\"><a href=\"#module-Z3\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">module</span> <a href=\"Z3/index.html\">Z3</a></span><span> : <span class=\"keyword\">sig</span> ... <span class=\"keyword\">end</span></span></code></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec module anchored\" id=\"module-Config\"><a href=\"#module-Config\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">module</span> <a href=\"Config/index.html\">Config</a></span><span> : <span class=\"keyword\">sig</span> ... <span class=\"keyword\">end</span></span></code></div></div>"}